4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE DEATH PENALTY;
5 PROVIDING THAT DEATH MUST BE CAUSED BY A SUBSTANCE OR SUBSTANCES IN A LETHAL
6 QUANTITY SUFFICIENT TO CAUSE DEATH; AND AMENDING SECTION 46-19-103, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 46-19-103, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "46-19-103. Execution of death sentence. (1) In pronouncing the sentence of death, the court shall
12 set the date of execution, which may not be less than 30 days or more than 60 days from the date the sentence
13 is pronounced. If execution has been stayed by any court and the date set for execution has passed prior to
14 dissolution of the stay, the court in which the defendant was previously sentenced shall, upon dissolution of the
15 stay, set a new date of execution for not less than 20 or more than 90 days from the day the date is set. The
16 defendant is entitled to be present in court on the day the new date of execution is set.
17 (2) Pending execution of a sentence of death, the sheriff may deliver the defendant to the Montana
18 state prison or the Montana women's prison for confinement, and the state shall bear the costs of imprisoning
19 the defendant from the date of delivery.
20 (3) The punishment of death must be inflicted by administration of a continuous, an intravenous
21 injection of a substance or substances in a lethal quantity of an ultra-fast-acting barbiturate in combination with
22 a chemical paralytic agent sufficient to cause death until a coroner or deputy coroner pronounces that the
23 defendant is dead.
24 (4) When an execution date is set, a death warrant signed by the judge and attested by the clerk of
25 court under the seal of the court must, within 5 days, be prepared. The warrant and a certified copy of the
26 judgment must be delivered to the director of the department of corrections. The warrant must be directed to
27 the director and recite the conviction, judgment, appointed date of execution, and duration of the warrant.
28 (5) The warden of the Montana state prison shall provide a suitable and efficient room or place in
